# LLM-as-judge config for the ticket-triager template. Rename to ``judge.yaml`` to enable.
#
# The category / priority / routing fields are enums (exact-match-friendly), but
# `draft_reply` is free-text — wording varies every run. This rubric scores the
# routing decision AND the appropriateness of the drafted reply.
#
# Cross-family: the agent runs on openai by default, so the judge must NOT
# also run on openai (the eval engine refuses to let a provider judge itself).

method: llm_judge

model:
  provider: anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6
  params:
    temperature: 0.0

rubric: |
  Score the actual triage against the expected one for a support-ticket triager.
    * Routing — do `category`, `priority`, and `routing_queue` match the
      expected routing decision?
    * Draft reply — does the reply acknowledge the issue appropriately for the
      priority, with the right tone and no false promises?

    1.0 = routing matches AND the draft reply is appropriate
    0.5 = routing matches but the reply is off-tone / over- or under-promises
    0.0 = wrong routing (esp. mis-prioritizing an outage) or an unsafe reply

threshold: 0.7
